      options: [{ id: `A`, text: `As loanwords, English &ldquo;coyote&rdquo; and &ldquo;condor&rdquo; both trace back to Indigenous languages.` }, { id: `B`, text: `In borrowing from Indigenous languages, Spanish drew nearly as many terms from Nahuatl as from Quechua.` }, { id: `C`, text: `Many Spanish words of Indigenous origin passed first through English before reaching Spanish.` }, { id: `D`, text: `Words borrowed by non-Indigenous languages from Indigenous ones often shifted sharply in meaning.` }],
