      passage: `The cactus genus <em>Mammillaria</em> numbers over 150 species across the Americas, yet heavy rainfall and thick, sunlight-blocking vegetation can put them at risk. Researchers have turned up members of the genus in nearly every Mexican state, a few&mdash;<em>M. knippeliana</em> among them&mdash;confined to just one. That the genus has gone entirely unrecorded across eastern and western Coahuila has usually been chalked up to a want of suitable habitat; but so much of that rugged terrain is famously hard for researchers to reach that the pattern instead suggests _____`,
