      passage: `Every recipient of the Nobel Prize in Literature has, as the prize&rsquo;s founder Alfred Nobel once put it, &ldquo;produced the most outstanding work in an idealistic _____ in 1912, for instance, judges recognized Gerhart Johann Robert Hauptmann [for] his fruitful, varied and outstanding production in the realm of dramatic art.&rdquo;`,
